# DATAGLOW — Supply-Chain Install Hardening
# ------------------------------------------------------------
# ignore-scripts: do NOT run any package's preinstall/install/postinstall
# lifecycle scripts on `npm install` / `npm ci`. Malicious install-time
# scripts are the most common software-supply-chain attack vector, so we
# opt out by default. DATAGLOW's two real runtime/dev DuckDB dependencies
# (@duckdb/duckdb-wasm, @duckdb/node-api) need NO install scripts to work,
# so nothing breaks. The one dependency that does declare an install script
# is the dev-only playwright-chromium (it downloads a browser); CI does not
# rely on that download because the e2e job installs and points at a real
# system Chrome instead. If a future dependency legitimately needs an install
# script, add an explicit `npm rebuild <pkg>` step in CI AND add it to the
# allowlist in .github/scripts/check-lifecycle-scripts.mjs — see AGENTS.md.
ignore-scripts=true

# min-release-age would block installing any version published in the last N
# days (a defense against freshly-published compromised releases), but it needs
# npm >= 11.10.0. The current CI/dev npm is 10.8.2, so the setting is a silent
# no-op there and is intentionally omitted rather than added dead. Re-add
# `min-release-age=7` once the toolchain moves to npm 11.10.0+.
